"""
small_cluster_orchestrator.py
==============================
Rubin Scalability Outside Hyperscale — NVL8 / Edge Cluster Optimizer.

PROBLEM: Scalability Outside Hyperscale
  Rubin NVL72 is designed for $300M+ AI factories.
  But many real customers have:
    • NVL8 nodes  (8 GPUs, 1 NVSwitch, no scale-out fabric)
    • 2-4 DGX Rubin nodes  (16-32 GPUs, InfiniBand/Spectrum-6)
    • On-premise clusters  (no photonic switches, limited bandwidth)
    • Edge deployments  (Rubin CPX with GDDR7, 128 GB, no HBM4)

  Challenges at this scale:
    1. MoE expert parallelism across only 8 GPUs creates hotspots
    2. KV cache doesn't fit in 288 GB per GPU for long-context requests
    3. NVLink-C2C with Vera requires careful memory management without
       the full 54 TB LPDDR5x of a rack
    4. Power management: NVL8 nodes at 30-40% load = terrible FLOPS/W
    5. Multi-tenant scheduling: multiple teams sharing one node

  This module provides orchestration primitives for sub-hyperscale Rubin.
"""

from __future__ import annotations

